align: left; }\r\n  table th { background: #f1f5f9; font-weight: 700; }\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"reg-wrap\">\r\n  <header class=\"reg-header\">\r\n    <div>\r\n      <h1>LEGO Sumo 1kg — Official Rules</h1>\r\n      <div class=\"meta\">Version 1.0 • Issued 2025-09-27 • Language: EN</div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <span class=\"reg-tag\">LEGO • Sumo Combat</span>\r\n  </header>\r\n\r\n  <section class=\"card\">\r\n    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>\r\n    <p>LEGO Sumo 1kg competition challenges teams to build powerful sumo robots using only LEGO components.</p>\r\n  </section>\r\n\r\n  <section class=\"card\">\r\n    <h2>2. Competition Overview</h2>\r\n    <p>Robots compete in sumo-style matches on a circular dohyo, attempting to push opponents out of the ring.</p>\r\n    <h3>2.1. Team Structure</h3>\r\n    <p>Maximum 5 team members, with only one operator allowed during matches.</p>\r\n    <h3>2.2. Age Categories</h3>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li><strong>Elementary (6-10):</strong> Basic LEGO sets allowed</li>\r\n      <li><strong>Middle School (10-14):</strong> Standard LEGO Mindstorms</li>\r\n      <li><strong>High School (14-18):</strong> Advanced LEGO techniques</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </section>\r\n\r\n  <section class=\"card\">\r\n    <h2>3. Robot Requirements</h2>\r\n    <h3>3.1. Construction Rules</h3>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li><strong>100% LEGO:</strong> Only official LEGO parts allowed</li>\r\n      <li><strong>Weight Limit:</strong> Maximum 1kg including all components</li>\r\n      <li><strong>Size Limit:</strong> Must fit in 15cm×15cm square at start</li>\r\n      <li><strong>Expansion:</strong> Robot may expand after match starts</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <table>\r\n      <thead><tr><th>Specification</th><th>Limit</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>\r\n      <tbody>\r\n        <tr><td>Weight</td><td>1kg</td><td>Including batteries</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>Initial Size</td><td>15×15cm</td><td>Height unlimited</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>Materials</td><td>LEGO only</td><td>Official parts only</td></tr>\r\n      </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n  </section>\r\n\r\n  <section class=\"card\">\r\n    <h2>4. Dohyo Specifications</h2>\r\n    <h3>4.1. Ring Dimensions</h3>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li><strong>Diameter:</strong> 77cm wooden circle</li>\r\n      <li><strong>Color:</strong> Black center (72cm) with white border (2.5cm)</li>\r\n      <li><strong>Height:</strong> 2-5cm above ground level</li>\r\n      <li><strong>Surface:</strong> Smooth, matte finish</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </section>\r\n\r\n  <section class=\"card\">\r\n    <h2>5. Match Rules</h2>\r\n    <h3>5.1. Match Format</h3>\r\n    <p>Best of 3 rounds, each round maximum 30 seconds. Robot that wins 2 rounds wins the match.</p>\r\n    <h3>5.2. Victory Conditions</h3>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li>Push opponent completely off the dohyo</li>\r\n      <li>Opponent becomes immobile for 10+ seconds</li>\r\n      <li>Opponent falls apart or stops functioning</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <h3>5.3. Starting Procedure</h3>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li>5-second countdown for autonomous start</li>\r\n      <li>Robots must be placed touching the white line</li>\r\n      <li>30-second adjustment period before each round</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </section>\r\n\r\n  <section class=\"card\">\r\n    <h2>6. Safety and Fair Play</h2>\r\n    <h3>6.1. Prohibited Actions</h3>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li>Damaging opponent\'s robot intentionally</li>\r\n      <li>Using sticky substances on wheels</li>\r\n      <li>Remote control during autonomous phase</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <div class=\"callout danger\">\r\n      <strong>Safety:</strong> Protective eyewear required for all participants.\r\n    </div>\r\n  </section>\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"foot\">Contact: <a href=\"mailto:office@relativity.ro\">office@relativity.ro</a></div>\r\n</div>', '2025-09-27 12:59:46', 0);
